  "body": "**Describe the bug**\r\n\r\nThe rate limiter implementation for the `reqresp` failed to validate the limit for a remaining limit. \r\n\r\ne.g. If remaining limit is 100 and currently you consumed 80 requests, you can still ask for the 200 more requests because the implementation validate the consumption before the increment. \r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/ChainSafe/lodestar/blob/222a91f3ac659db0feb6f7e9621ebeea8ebb085c/packages/beacon-node/src/network/reqresp/rateTracker.ts#L30\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/ChainSafe/lodestar/blob/222a91f3ac659db0feb6f7e9621ebeea8ebb085c/packages/beacon-node/src/network/reqresp/rateTracker.ts#L36\r\n\r\n**Expected behavior**\r\n\r\nIt should not allow to over-limit in any case. \r\n\r\n",
